  "local_port": 42948,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do I get snapchat notifications of some people but not others?",
  "response": "Snapchat notifications can be customized based on your preferences, which might explain why you receive notifications from some people but not others. Here are a few reasons and steps you can take to manage your Snapchat notifications:\n\n1. **Custom Notification Settings for Friends:**\n   Snapchat allows you to set custom notifications for specific friends. If you've set custom notifications for some friends and not others, you'll receive notifications only from those with custom settings.\n   - To check or set custom notifications, go to your Snapchat settings, then to \"Notifications,\" and look for \"Custom Notifications.\" From there, you can select friends and choose what types of notifications you want to receive from them.\n\n2. **Snapchat+ Subscription:**\n   If you or the other person has a Snapchat+ subscription, it might affect notification settings. Snapchat+ offers additional features and might have different notification settings.\n\n3. **Friend's Notification Settings:**\n   The person sending you snaps or messages might have their settings configured in a way that doesn't trigger notifications on your end. They might have turned off certain types of notifications or set specific times when notifications are sent.\n\n4. **General Notification Settings:**\n   Check your general notification settings for Snapchat on your device. Sometimes, these settings can override app-specific settings.\n   - On iOS: Go to Settings > Snapchat > Notifications.\n   - On Android: Go to Settings > Apps > Snapchat > Notifications.\n\n5. **App Version and Updates:**\n   Make sure your Snapchat app is up to date. Sometimes, bugs in older versions can affect notifications.\n\n6. **Do Not Disturb or Focus Modes:**\n   If your device is in Do Not Disturb mode or using Focus modes, it might block notifications from certain apps or contacts.\n\n7. **Snapchat's Algorithm:**\n   Snapchat uses algorithms to prioritize notifications based on your interactions. If you interact more with certain friends, you might receive their notifications more frequently.\n\nTo troubleshoot, you can:\n- Review and adjust your notification settings within Snapchat.\n- Check your device's notification settings for Snapchat.\n- Ensure that neither you nor your friends are in modes that block notifications.\n- Update the Snapchat app to the latest version.\n\nIf issues persist, you might want to contact Snapchat support for further assistance.",
